---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";

// AT&T iPhone trade-in decode. Every quote below is verbatim from a stored
// snapshot of AT&T's public trade-in deals page. Source and capture date are
// rendered under each quote. The two AT&T terms pages that would carry the
// promotion's fine print (tradein.att.com/offer-details and
// tradein.att.com/terms-conditions) were captured on the same date but returned
// a "JavaScript is deactivated" stub with no terms text, so their language is
// not in the archive and is not quoted here.

const deals = {
  target: "terms_att_tradein_deals",
  source: "att.com/deals/phone-trade-in",
  url: "https://www.att.com/deals/phone-trade-in/",
  captured: "2026-07-21",
  archive: null, // no archive snapshot captured for this record
};
---

<Base
  title="AT&T iPhone trade-in, decoded"
  description="The AT&T iPhone trade-in promotion advertised as iPhone on us, up to $1,100 off, set against the binding trade-in terms quoted verbatim from AT&T's own published pages."
>
  <div class="wrap prose" data-pagefind-body>
    <p class="crumb"><a href="/decoded">The Offer, Decoded</a></p>
    <h1>AT&T: iPhone on us, up to $1,100 off</h1>

    <h2>The advertised offer</h2>
    <p>
      AT&T advertised the iPhone 17 Pro on us, up to $1,100 off, with a
      qualifying trade-in. That is the offer as advertised. Below is what AT&T's
      own published trade-in pages say about how the trade-in and its credits
      work.
    </p>

    <p class="note-inline">
      Every quote below is reproduced word for word from a stored snapshot of the
      AT&T page named under it, captured on the date shown. Where the captured
      page stored a line in an unusual or incomplete form, it is reproduced as
      stored.
    </p>

    <h2>What you trade in</h2>

    <figure class="quote">
      <blockquote>
        <p>You may submit up to five devices during a twelve-month period.</p>
      </blockquote>
      <figcaption>
        AT&T, <a href={deals.url} rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">{deals.source}</a>,
        captured {deals.captured} (target {deals.target}).
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <figure class="quote">
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          If you’re on an installment plan with your old carrier, you’ll first
          need to pay off the device before trading it into AT&T. Otherwise, your
          old carrier may bill you for what you owe for the device.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
      <figcaption>
        AT&T, <a href={deals.url} rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">{deals.source}</a>,
        captured {deals.captured} (target {deals.target}).
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>How the credit arrives</h2>

    <p>
      The captured page states the promotional bill credit in this form:
    </p>

    <figure class="quote">
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          For trade-in value received as part of a trade-in promotion, bill
          credits will be applied to your AT&T account in equal amounts over $30.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
      <figcaption>
        AT&T, <a href={deals.url} rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">{deals.source}</a>,
        captured {deals.captured} (target {deals.target}).
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <figure class="quote">
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          If you’re trading in your device as part of a national trade-in
          promotion, your eligible promotional credit will be applied to your
          bill within 3 billing cycles.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
      <figcaption>
        AT&T, <a href={deals.url} rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">{deals.source}</a>,
        captured {deals.captured} (target {deals.target}).
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <figure class="quote">
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          Once AT&T receives your old phone and verifies its condition, you will
          get an AT&T Promotion Card credited with your phone’s value or the
          value of your device offer as a bill credit.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
      <figcaption>
        AT&T, <a href={deals.url} rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">{deals.source}</a>,
        captured {deals.captured} (target {deals.target}).
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>What ends the credits</h2>

    <figure class="quote">
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          Note: You must ship your old device within thirty (30) days of
          activating your new device to remain eligible for promotional credit.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
      <figcaption>
        AT&T, <a href={deals.url} rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">{deals.source}</a>,
        captured {deals.captured} (target {deals.target}).
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <figure class="quote">
      <blockquote>
        <p>Send us your old device within 30 days of activating your new one.</p>
      </blockquote>
      <figcaption>
        AT&T, <a href={deals.url} rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">{deals.source}</a>,
        captured {deals.captured} (target {deals.target}).
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>What happens to your old phone</h2>

    <figure class="quote">
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          Before mailing, turn off activation locks like Find My iPhone and
          Google activation locks to limit processing delays and avoid losing
          your trade-in value.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
      <figcaption>
        AT&T, <a href={deals.url} rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">{deals.source}</a>,
        captured {deals.captured} (target {deals.target}).
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <figure class="quote">
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          If your old device shows signs of wear, it will still be accepted, but
          the value will be adjusted accordingly.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
      <figcaption>
        AT&T, <a href={deals.url} rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">{deals.source}</a>,
        captured {deals.captured} (target {deals.target}).
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <figure class="quote">
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          If the trade-in value of a device is zero, you can mail your device in
          for recycling.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
      <figcaption>
        AT&T, <a href={deals.url} rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">{deals.source}</a>,
        captured {deals.captured} (target {deals.target}).
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>What these captured terms do not answer</h2>
    <p>
      Two questions in the brief for this page have no supporting quote in the
      snapshots, so those sections are left out. The captured pages also leave
      several parts of the advertised offer unstated. As captured on
      {" "}{deals.captured}, the AT&T trade-in pages do not state:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        the advertised amount or device. The words iPhone 17 Pro and up to $1,100
        appear in the advertisement, not in the trade-in terms we captured.
      </li>
      <li>
        a total number of months or a total dollar figure for the promotional
        bill credit. The captured page says credits arrive in equal amounts and
        within 3 billing cycles, and states the schedule as reproduced above.
      </li>
      <li>
        what happens to the credits if wireless service is cancelled, a line is
        removed, or the plan is changed.
      </li>
      <li>
        what a customer owes on the financed device if they leave before the
        credits finish. No section on early exit appears, so none is shown here.
      </li>
      <li>
        whether the traded-in device is ever returned to the customer.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The two AT&T pages that would carry this fine print,
      tradein.att.com/offer-details and tradein.att.com/terms-conditions, were
      captured on {deals.captured} but returned a page reading only that
      JavaScript is deactivated, with no terms text to quote. When a readable
      capture of those pages exists, their language will be added here.
    </p>

    <h2>Next</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/ask">Ask the evidence</a> a question about carrier promotions.</li>
      <li><a href="/tell">Tell your story</a> if this happened to you.</li>
      <li><a href="/take-action">Take action</a> with the FCC or your state attorney general.</li>
      <li><a href="/methodology">Methodology</a> for how the terms archive is captured.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <style>
    .crumb {
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }
    .note-inline {
      max-width: var(--measure);
      border-left: 4px solid var(--border);
      padding-left: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--text-soft);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
    .quote {
      max-width: var(--measure);
      margin: 1.25rem 0;
    }
    .quote blockquote {
      margin: 0;
      border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
      background: var(--surface);
      border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
      padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    }
    .quote blockquote p {
      margin: 0;
    }
    .quote figcaption {
      margin-top: 0.4rem;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      color: var(--text-soft);
    }
  </style>
</Base>
